                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00/1897</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 26</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch of
                    August 5, 1922, discussing the political situation in Haiti and transmitting a
                    copy of a proclamation issued by you to the Haitian people.</p>
                <p>Your action in this matter is approved, but the Department would prefer that it
                    be consulted in the future before any proclamations of general political
                    importance are issued.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
